Package com.destroystokyo.paper.utils

Class PriorityQueuedExecutor

java.lang.Object
java.util.concurrent.AbstractExecutorService
com.destroystokyo.paper.utils.PriorityQueuedExecutor
All Implemented Interfaces:
AutoCloseable, Executor, ExecutorService
public class PriorityQueuedExecutor extends AbstractExecutorService
Implements an Executor Service that allows specifying Task Priority and bumping of task priority. This is a non blocking executor with 3 priority levels. URGENT: Rarely used, something that is critical to take action now. HIGH: Something with more importance than the base tasks
